### Conclusion

The discrepancy was resolved by ensuring the Python code uses the polynomial CDF approximation consistently, removing the `scipy.stats.norm` dependency. The updated project maintains the professional narrative and scikit-learn-style structure, delivering accurate results that match the manual calculations. This version is ready for your GitHub portfolio to impress employers. If you’d like further enhancements (e.g., visualizations, additional Greeks), or have other projects to explore, please let me know!


